messages.text: OMG! It felt so good to kiss you last night!!!
:-) LOL
LOL???
Are you laughing at me?
NO! I’m just *very happy* about your text!
(Aaand… you’re a crazy girl!)
Why???
Don’t get upset, I mean it in a good way…
Actually, in the best possible way!
Why do you think I’m crazy? Didn’t you like kissing me? I mean it was FANTASTIC!
It was perfect like in a movie, but it was real.
You’re right! It felt fantastic for me too. I just never met anyone as… direct as you, Julia.
Is that a bad thing?
No, not at all. It’s just that sometimes you… surprise me and I don’t know what to say.
Just say how you feel, and you’ll be fine. ;-)
Well, then… I like you very much! :-)
See? It’s easy! :-P
Seriously, I can’t believe how lucky we were last night… finding those candles by the beach
and my favorite song played by that car from afar! it just felt like the stars aligned to make that moment happen.
(BTW I really like you too)
:-))) Well… since we’re being honest… it wasn’t all luck!
“Whaddayoumean” (as J Bieber would say)
LOL Ehm… I had planned A LITTLE for the moment!
Really???
… the candles…
But you said someone must have left them from a previous picnic or something??!
Yeah, sorry I lied! I didn’t want to make it look like I was dying to kiss you!
Also, I didn’t know if you would find it lame.
LAME???!
Who’s the monster who finds candles by the beach LAME???
Well, now I know you liked it! :-) Phew!
What about the song? Was that planned too?
Let’s just say I’m gonna have to wash my bigger brother’s car for the next 3 weeks…!
Wow! You REALLY planned everything!
Are you mad?
No! But… I’m surprised! (I guess this is my turn!)
LOL yeah!
So… I mean… you liked me for quite some time? I mean, if you took the time to plan this…
Uhm, yeah. I’m afraid I liked you since the Bonfire in 5th grade!
But that’s like… 2 years ago!
I guess!
Why didn’t you say anything?
I was afraid you wouldn’t like me back.
I thought you were into Jeremy…
I was NOT!
Why does everybody think I’m into Jeremy!? Grr!
I don’t know, it MAY be because you guys always leave school together…!
Whaaat?? We just live next to each other! I’ve known him since pre-k! He’s like… a cousin!
But you KISSED your cousin at the Bonfire!!!
I didn’t kiss him!
Everybody saw your shadows in the tent!
Are you serious? I mean, I can’t tell you what happened because it’s rather disgusting.
But it was definitely nothing romantic!!!
Now I want to know more!
Jeremy made me swear I’d never share this with a living soul.
Well, I’ll pretend to be a zombie then! It’s almost Halloween after all! :-))
OK. But don’t tell anyone.
Scout’s honor.
I was helping him get rid of a piece of a marshmallow stuck in his teeth because he wanted to try to kiss Katrin.
ROFL
This isn’t true! Please, tell me it’s not true because I’m laughing to death.
It is true!!! I swear to the God of marshmallows.
That is so funny!!!
Your turn now!
My turn?
I want a secret!
Mmm… I have one, but maybe it’s not something that you’d like to know…
Of course it’s something I want to know!
Sure?
YES PLEASE I’M DYING TO KNOW IT NOW!
I had never kissed anyone before you.
It felt like a million stars falling on me and tickling my skin and I think I’ll never forget it.
Are you still there?
Yes, I’m here
Too much honesty?
No np
You sound… spooked?
I didn’t mean to spook you. Sorry! I just wanted to tell you how great you made me feel. That’s all.
I mean, I’m sure you kissed other boys so maybe you think I’m cheesy now… :(
Please don’t tell anyone!!!
Scout’s honor!
And… I felt the stars thing too.
Really?
Yes… where does that leave us?
Whaddayamean
I mean… are you my boyfriend?
I don’t know how these things work.
Yeah… me neither! :-)))
But I would love to be your boyfriend.
Seriously?
Yeah!
OK THEN!
What do we do now?
I can’t wait to see you tomorrow at school!
Me too…
I wasn’t sure it was OK to text you today… but now that you’re my girlfriend… that means I can text you whenever I want?
I guess!
and you won’t get spooked?
If I get spooked I’ll tell you… do you think that’s going to work?
It sounds perfect!
I’m so happy!!!!
Me too :-)))
Well, goodnight Bruce! I’d love an app to send you a million kisses like shooting stars all over your face.
I hope to dream about it! Good night Julia! <3
